Quiz 42 Global Illumination

1. Which of the following scenes would make the most noticeable use of GI?

- A room with sunlight streaming in through a small opening

2. Why is the wall to the centre-right green in the following image?

- It is reflecting ligh off the right most wall

3. What are the limitation sof GI in Unity?

- It cannot be done at run-time

4. Which of the following methods fo GI is best suited to mobile?

- Baked

5. Which method of illumination can cope with non-static objects in a scene?

- Direct Illumination

6. What does the Baked Resolution control?

- The resolution of the GI cache per Unity unit

7. How does final gather work?

- It computes the last bounce of light at full Baked Resolution